This article is a presidential memorandum issued by President Barack Obama on January 16, 2013. The memorandum addresses the issue of gun violence in the United States, stating that it is not only a law enforcement challenge but also a serious public health issue. The memorandum directs the Secretary of Health and Human Services to conduct or sponsor research into the causes of gun violence and ways to prevent it. It emphasizes the importance of taking a broader public health perspective in developing comprehensive strategies to address this issue. The memorandum also includes general provisions regarding its implementation and publication.